  "title": "Officer, HSSSE & Facilities",
  "description": "<p><strong>The Job:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Implementing and monitoring HSSSE programs, policies, and compliance with statutory requirements.</p></li><li><p>Conducting workplace inspections, risk assessments, audits, and safety briefings.</p></li><li><p>Managing facility operations, preventive and corrective maintenance, and contractor activities.</p></li><li><p>Supporting emergency preparedness, incident response, and business continuity planning.</p></li><li><p>Maintaining HSSSE and facility records, reporting performance, and recommending improvements.</p></li><li><p>Overseeing environmental hygiene, waste management, and sustainability initiatives.</p></li></ul><p><strong>The Person:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Proficient in MS Office.</p></li><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Facilities Management, Building Services, Mechanical/Electrical Engineering, or a related field.</p></li><li><p>Relevant certifications such as Fire Safety Manager (FSM), Workplace Safety and Health (WSH), or Energy Management are an advantage.</p></li><li><p>Preferably holds a valid Licensed Electrical Worker (LEW) certification.</p></li><li><p>Minimum 3–5 years of experience in facilities or building management, including hands-on maintenance and contractor supervision.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Job summary</strong></p><p>Create a top-notch workplace! Oversee operations, maintenance, and vendors to keep our office safe, efficient, and welcoming.</p><p>Key selling points</p><ul><li>Work-life-balance (Monday - Friday 8AM-530PM)</li><li>Medical and Dental Benefits</li><li>Training Provided</li></ul>",
